      	<article allWordsNum="93">
            	<![CDATA[
With their trunks (树干) all bent towards the north, the trees look like something out of a fairy tale.
In a small forest in Poland, about 400 strange pine trees (松树) grow with a 90 degree bend right at the base of the tree trunks, and all bend towards the north for some reason. These pine trees in the forest were planted around 1930.
Someone says that people at that time made the trees grow in this way. They used the trees to make bent-wood furniture, and creat a memorable experience for anyone visiting Poland.
        	]]>
